  "text": "While it is clear that linear summation acts to reduce the number of independent inputs possible from a given texture class, it is equally clear that that nonlinear interactions can increase the alphabet size. [CITATION_1] ). Notice that the Allan Variance measure we selected has the form (a− b) 2 , being based on the square of local differences of mean receptive field output in response to mini-texture input. As outlined in Section 2, the Allan Variance and its derivatives may have some utility compared to traditional variance measures, and is related to wavelet variance [CITATION_2] .",
